# (to look) [[worried]], [[bothered]], [[annoyed]] (''avoir l'air ennuyé'')
# {{lb|fr|rarely}} [[bored]], {{l|en|ennuyé}}

====Usage notes====
The expression ''je suis ennuyé'' is a common incorrect way that English speakers try to say ''I'm bored'' ("je m'[[ennuyer|ennuie]]"). It in fact means "I'm upset" or several other similar or quite different things depending on the context. The same holds true for ''je suis {{m|fr|embêté}}'' (instead of "je m'[[embête]]").
